<A NAME=author><H2>About the author</H2></A>
<TABLE WIDTH=100% CELLPADDING=15>
<TR><TD ALIGN=center VALIGN=middle><IMG
  SRC=markov.gif WIDTH=135 HEIGHT=194 BORDER=0></TD>
    <TD VALIGN=top>
<A HREF=http://mark.overmeer.net>Mark Overmeer</A> got his MSc in
  Informatics from the <A HREF=http://www.kun.nl>University of Nijmegen</A>,
  NL in 1990.  Since then, he gained professional experience in maintaining
  a large variety of UNIX-systems, from tiny to super-computers.
  In his current occupation, this knowledge is taught to system-developers
  and -maintainers at <A HREF=http://www.ATComputing.nl>AT Computing bv</A>,
  a leading training institute on UNIX and UNIX-related languages in the
  Netherlands.
  <P>
  Next to his professional activities in computers, he maintains a very
  popular <A HREF=http://www.dhp.nl>Dutch Internet-site</A> since 1995,
  and actively participates in development of Public Domain software.
</TD></TR>
